1. use email template and email-styles.css to create email.
2. using the following tool, paste css inside a head/style tag, removing body tag. Run the tool.

    http://templates.mailchimp.com/resources/inline-css/
    \

 3. take result and paste into a new email file adding -inline.html to the filename.
 4. remove head and body tags.
 5. create template on Sparkpost using this html.
 5.5 send test from template and verfiy all looks right in all clients and links work as expected.
 6. update recipient list on sparkpost.
 7. note the list ID and template ID for the email blast.
 8. using POSTMAN, post to sparkpost API, in the body use the SparkPostAPI.json file.


